parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause a loss of braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or near-accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brakes pulsate or make a loud noise
the brake pedal becomes hard or travels to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the brakes fail to engage or release properly
the vehicle is difficult to stop or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause uneven braking, pulsating brakes, and extended stopping distances, which can lead to accidents or near-accidents.
symptoms: The brakes pulsate or make a loud noise
the brake pedal vibrates or feels spongy
the vehicle experiences uneven braking or extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or near-accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard or travels to the floor
the brakes fail to engage or release properly
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the brakes pulsate or make a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Catalytic Converter Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, while the catalytic converter failure can lead to increased emissions, decreased performance, and potentially cause a fire.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls frequently
the catalytic converter is smoking excessively
the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak can cause damage to the engine and surrounding components, leading to premature wear and potentially catastrophic failure.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the valve cover
oil spots under the vehicle
increased oil consumption.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective head engine gasket can cause coolant or oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially catastrophic failure.
symptoms: Coolant or oil leaking from the head engine gasket
engine overheating
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and bucking can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to engine failure, resulting in a safety risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates
bucks
and jumps in and out of gears while driving
causing the vehicle to jerk or lurch
making it difficult to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The axle failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to a vehicle fire, resulting in a safety risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The axle breaks or fails while driving
causing the vehicle to lose control
and potentially leading to a fire.
